## Standard production refresh (recommended)

```bash
# 1. Incremental index update (safe — production keeps serving during GHA)
gh workflow run refresh-docs.yml --ref main
# or: gh workflow run refresh-docs.yml --ref main -f force=false

# 2. Verify GHA logs: ingest Done, Collection now has ~33k+ chunks, S3 upload ~300MB

# 3. Controlled Railway reload (maintenance window ~2–4 min)
STARTED=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)
railway variables \
  --set "KNOWLEDGE_BANK_UPDATING=true" \
  --set "KNOWLEDGE_BANK_UPDATE_STARTED_AT=$STARTED" \
  --set "FORCE_CHROMA_RESTORE=true" \
  --set "CHROMA_RESTORE_ETA_MINUTES=4"
railway redeploy -y

# 4. Poll until document_count matches GHA (e.g. 41005)
curl -s https://experienceleaguechatbotaws-production.up.railway.app/api/health

# 5. Unset flags — do NOT redeploy (redeploy wipes /tmp and risks 0-chunk outage)
railway variables \
  --set "FORCE_CHROMA_RESTORE=false" \
  --set "KNOWLEDGE_BANK_UPDATING=false" \
  --set "KNOWLEDGE_BANK_UPDATE_STARTED_AT="
```

**Preferred:** use the safe wrapper (sets `CHROMA_PERSIST_DIR`, one redeploy, no step-5 redeploy):

```bash
./scripts/railway_chroma_reload.sh
```

